title: Precision Opinions Live
description:
Welcome to Precision Opinions Live! A podcast and videocast, hosted by Christian Stella (Pharm D, ABAAHP), that discusses different topics within the pharmaceutical, compounding and medical world. 

Precision Opinions Live is recorded inside the offices of Precision Compounding Pharmacy, located in Bellmore New York. 
Being inside an active pharmacy, we are able to use the podcast and videocast platforms to further assist the pharmacy's customers and partners while being on the front lines of pharmaceutical trends and consumer needs. 

Christian Stella and guests provide information and technical insight to both patients and other professionals, as well as offering an avenue for answering any compounding or pharmaceutical questions submitted to the show anonymously. 

Having previously been a guest on shows like; Optimal Health with Dr. Christopher Calapai on WABC 770am, and the LDN Radio show, Christian Stella has taken the next step in providing you the listener with even more opportunities to expand your understanding of medications and pharmaceuticals, by starting Precision Opinions Live.

"If I can help one patient better understand what they are taking, why something may or may not be providing the results they are looking for or even simply help them use their medication safely and correctly, then Precision Opinions Live has done it's job" says Christian Stella, Pharm D ABAAHP and host of Precision Opinions Live. 

"Sometimes patients or even other industry professionals are unaware of all of the options that are available to them. By bringing in different guests ranging from doctors with large practices to students, there is a greater chance of connecting that one listener struggling with a medical issue, to the medical professional who can better assist them."    

So join us here at Precision Opinions Live, on our journey to a better understanding of how different pharmaceuticals work and a healthier future.
  
The show can also be viewed on our Youtube channel (all links below) and new updates are always posted on our Instagram, Facebook and Linkedin accounts.

title: My Gut Feelings
description: The answer to most digestive ailments today results from poor choices in our diet,  chronic stress and alterations in the microbiome or gut bacteria. Medical research has drastically changed our understanding of many G.I. diseases. Stomach ulcers are no known to be caused by an infection with H. pylori bacteria. So successful eradication of the infection prevents stomach ulcers from recurring. Bleeding ulcers and esophageal ulceration from acid reflux is rarely seen now with a very potent proton pump inhibitors such as omeprazole. On the other hand autoimmune disease of the bowel such as Crohn's disease or ulcerative colitis is on the increase although biologic agents are now able to alter the disease course so that the overall prognosis is better in these patients. Irritable bowel syndrome is more often diagnosed and its treatment leaves much to be desired. Screening colonoscopy has decreased the death rate from colon cancer. We also have a better understanding of anorectal disease and it's management. I am a professor of Medicine and have been practicing for over 30 years and offer my insights into our digestive wellbeing.

Well, girl, I am so excited you’re here!

In this podcast, you will learn how to regulate your period naturally, decrease mood swings (yes, even postpartum!), eliminate headaches, and enjoy sex again!

I’m Dominique, a mom, military wife, daughter of Jesus, and women’s hormone specialist! I remember a time when I suffered with the worst period cramps and migraines. Then, after my first daughter, I suffered from postpartum depression. However, I did not want the new form of birth control that everyone told me to try. I wanted to get to the root cause of my problems and not just slap a “band-aid” on them. So I went back to school (yes with a new baby and a toddler) for my Master of Science in Nutrition Sciences with my focus in women’s hormones.

I learned how to heal my hormones and created a plan that was easy, natural, and doable because that’s what I needed as a busy mom of littles. And now I’m ready to share everything I’ve learned with you.

If you are ready to finally get to the root cause of your period problems, mood swings, and lack of sex drive, then grab your notebook and pen (or crayon if that’s all you can find), your beverage of choice, and get ready to listen in!

title: Basic Nutrish
description:
Welcome to "Basic Nutrish" with Lauran Martyn – the podcast that fills in the gaps in your nutritional knowledge, from childhood straight through to the complexities of adulthood. 🎧🥦

Lauran Martyn is a Certified Nutrition Coach, Strength & Conditioning Specialist with 6+ years of coaching and training experience working with local, in-person clients and virtual clients all over the world.

In a world overflowing with diet trends and conflicting information, it's time to get back to the basics that should have been part of our foundational education. Join Lauran as she breaks down essential nutrition principles in a clear and engaging way, making sure you have the tools you need to make informed choices about what you put on your plate.

Whether you're a recent graduate navigating your newfound independence, a busy professional juggling responsibilities, or anyone seeking to better understand the impact of food on your well-being, Basic Nutrish has something for you. Lauran's passion for demystifying nutrition shines through as she explores topics that are relevant to your everyday life.

Bonus Content for those who hunger for a deeper dive. By becoming a Patreon subscriber, you'll unlock a treasure trove of exclusive content. Enjoy extended podcast episodes where Lauran goes beyond the basics, delving into the nuances of nutrition that truly matter, downloadable worksheets and comprehensive guides will help you translate knowledge into action, turning intentions into habits.

Click this link to become a Patron - patreon.com/basicnutrish

"Basic Nutrish" isn't just a podcast; it's a journey towards empowerment. It's about understanding the essential building blocks of a healthy life and equipping yourself with the information you need to thrive. So, whether you're on your daily commute, hitting the gym, or simply unwinding at home, let Lauran Martyn be your guide to a more informed and nourished you.

Subscribe now and become a valued member of the "Basic Nutrish" community. Together, let's embrace the knowledge we all deserve and create a healthier future, one fundamental at a time. 🌱🍎
